  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1">Console Connection Issues</para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Normal">For refused, timed-out, or silent console connections, the full client coverage is in the Terminal Clients page. In brief, check three things:</para>
    <para styleclass="NotesBox">The listener is up -- the log shows &quot;Listening on TCP port ...&quot;.</para>
    <para styleclass="NotesBox">The port matches your client (the default is 10023; an instance may have been started on another with EMULATR_CONSOLE_PORT).</para>
    <para styleclass="NotesBox">The client is in RAW mode -- the socket is raw, with no Telnet option negotiation.</para>
    <para styleclass="Normal"></para>
